    {
      "type": "teaser",
      "visible": true,
      "title": "",
      "content": {
        "media": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "src": "assets/img-000.png",
            "caption": "GLD diffuses in geometric feature space, enabling both RGB and geometry decoding with 4.4× faster convergence.",
            "alt": "Figure 1 — Comparison of VAE latent diffusion vs Geometric Latent Diffusion (GLD), with training efficiency plot showing 4.4× faster convergence."
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "03ebf5d8",
      "paddingBottom": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "tldr",
      "visible": true,
      "title": "TL;DR",
      "content": {
        "text": "We propose **Geometric Latent Diffusion (GLD)**, a framework that repurposes the feature space of geometric foundation models (e.g., Depth Anything 3) as the latent space for multi-view diffusion. GLD achieves state-of-the-art novel view synthesis with **4.4× faster training convergence** than VAE-based approaches — all trained from scratch without any text-to-image pretraining."
      },
      "id": "071e9da1",
      "paddingBottom": 0,
      "paddingTop": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "visible": true,
      "title": "~#7b4b1e:Geometric Feature Space as Diffusion Latent~",
      "content": {
        "bulletItems": [
          "**Geometry as latent space.** The first framework to repurpose a geometric foundation model's feature space as the diffusion latent space — DA3 features encode both high-fidelity RGB (**35.41 dB** PSNR) and strong cross-view correspondences ($\\text{PCK}=35.98$, surpassing DINOv2's $31.64$).",
          "**State-of-the-art NVS from scratch.** Outperforms all baselines on in-domain benchmarks (Re10K, DL3DV) in both 2D and 3D metrics, and remains competitive out-of-domain — without any text-to-image pretraining.",
          "**Zero-shot geometry for free.** Depth maps and 3D point clouds are decoded directly from synthesized latents via the frozen DA3 decoder, with no additional training required."
        ]
      },
      "id": "1c337394",
      "paddingBottom": 68,
      "paddingTop": 28,
      "sectionLabel": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "visible": true,
      "sectionLabel": "Method",
      "title": "~#7b4b1e:A Three-Stage Pipeline~\n",
      "content": {
        "media": [],
        "columns": 1,
        "imageGridRows": 1,
        "objectFit": "cover",
        "text": "## Stage 1 — Can DA3 features reconstruct images?\n\nWe first validate that the frozen DA3 encoder's feature space is expressive enough for high-fidelity image generation."
      },
      "id": "ca1ff273",
      "paddingBottom": 8,
      "paddingTop": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "c66be766",
      "type": "image-grid",
      "visible": true,
      "content": {
        "columns": 2,
        "imageGridRows": 1,
        "media": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "src": "assets/img-013.png",
            "caption": ""
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "src": "assets/img-014.png",
            "caption": ""
          }
        ]
      },
      "title": "",
      "paddingBottom": 0,
      "paddingTop": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "visible": true,
      "sectionLabel": "",
      "title": "",
      "content": {
        "text": "",
        "bulletItems": [
          "**RGB decoder training.** A ViT-based decoder $D_\\text{rgb}$ is trained to reconstruct RGB images from DA3's multi-level features $\\{F_l\\}$ ($L=4$ levels), extracted by the frozen encoder.",
          "**Level-wise dropout.** Individual feature levels are randomly masked during training, forcing the decoder to reconstruct from partial inputs and improving robustness.",
          "**Result: 35.41 dB PSNR** on Re10K (4,000 test samples) — competitive with the Stable Diffusion VAE (34.53 dB) and SDXL VAE (34.97 dB), confirming the feature space is suitable for diffusion."
        ]
      },
      "id": "0a90db0d-s1",
      "paddingTop": 0,
      "paddingBottom": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "29197bec",
      "type": "text",
      "visible": true,
      "content": {
        "text": "## Stage 2 — Optimal boundary layer selection\n\nDiffusing all four feature levels is computationally prohibitive, so we identify an optimal boundary layer k: features up to level k are explicitly synthesized by the diffusion model, while deeper features are deterministically derived by propagating through the frozen DA3 encoder. \n\nAll models adopt the DiT architecture with flow-matching training, 3D self-attention with RoPE for cross-view reasoning, and Plücker ray conditioning to ensure geometric consistency."
      },
      "title": "",
      "paddingBottom": 19,
      "paddingTop": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "1fe39e0d",
      "type": "image-grid",
      "visible": true,
      "content": {
        "media": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "src": "assets/img-015.png",
            "caption": "",
            "alt": ""
          }
        ],
        "columns": 1,
        "imageGridRows": 1
      },
      "title": "",
      "paddingBottom": 24,
      "paddingTop": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "visible": true,
      "sectionLabel": "",
      "title": "",
      "content": {
        "text": "## Stage 3 — Cascaded feature generation\n\nWith the boundary set at $k=1$, two multi-view diffusion models generate the explicit feature levels in a cascaded manner.",
        "bulletItems": [
          "$\\mathcal{M}_0$ synthesizes level-1 features. $\\mathcal{M}_{1 \\to 0}$ then generates level-0 features conditioned on the synthesized level-1 output, ensuring cross-level alignment.",
          "**Feature propagation.** Deeper features (levels 2–3) are deterministically derived by passing synthesized level-1 features through the frozen DA3 encoder — no additional diffusion needed.",
          "**RGB & geometry decoding.** The full multi-level feature set is decoded into target views via $D_\\text{rgb}$, and into depth maps and camera poses via the frozen DA3 geometric decoder $D_\\text{geo}$ — zero-shot, without any fine-tuning."
        ]
      },
      "id": "0a90db0d-s3",
      "paddingTop": 0,
      "paddingBottom": 68
    },
